The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, April 15 (PTI): A Delhi court today summoned Bollywood actor and producer Aamir Khan to depose as a witness in a seven-year-old copyright violation case relating to his film Lagaan.          
	Delhi police had seized seven VCDs of Lagaan and 34 VCDs of Gadar from the accused, Risabh Chawla, on June 22, 2001. The complainant, Anil Malhotra, has said he had the copyright for these films. Khan was made a witness in the case since Lagaan had been produced under his banner.                   
	Vadodara (PTI): A woman was injured when two masked men on a motorbike threw acid at her while she was standing outside her home, police said on Tuesday. Shobhna Raval had opposed a housing construction scheme for the poor in her locality saying the plot was reserved for a garden and community centre.                  
	Kanpur (PTI): Two youths pierced their bodies with pins in front of a statue of Babasaheb Ambedkar on his 117th birth anniversary on Monday to protest unemployment. They shaved their heads and wrote Ambedkars name on their foreheads. They were later arrested and sent to hospital.                   
	New Delhi (PTI): The government will increase the digits in the postal index number (PIN) from six to eight to ensure speedy delivery of post. The last two numbers in the eight-digit PIN will help identify a specific mohalla (colony), the director of postal services said. The PIN will be used in future to sort post by machines.                   
	 Jaipur (PTI): A woman and two girls were killed and four persons injured when a pickup truck ran over them as they slept on the roadside. The injured have been admitted to hospital. The driver fled, leaving the vehicle behind.                                                                                                                         
